  {
    q: "Do septic tank treatments actually work?",
    a: "Used consistently, yes — the good ones. They replenish the bacteria that break down solids and keep the system flowing, which reduces odors, slows sludge build-up, and lengthens the time between pump-outs. What they can't do is replace pumping entirely or fix a mechanical fault. Treat them as ongoing maintenance, not a one-time cure.",
  },
  {
    q: "How often should I treat my septic tank?",
    a: "Most treatments, including our top pick, are designed for a monthly dose after an initial heavier treatment. Setting a recurring monthly reminder is the single easiest way to keep a system healthy — the most common reason treatments 'don't work' is that people forget to keep using them.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is Septifix safe for my tank and the environment?",
    a: "It's designed to be. The tablets use naturally-occurring bacteria plus an oxygen-releasing compound, with no harsh chemicals that would harm the tank, the drain field, or groundwater. As with any treatment, follow the dosing on the label rather than overdosing.",
