  {
    q: "Septifix vs. Rid-X — which should I buy?",
    a: "Rid-X is the supermarket option, and it does a reasonable job of digesting solids. What it doesn't do is release oxygen — and that's the step that actually attacks the rotten-egg smell rather than just masking it. It's also a powder you measure and pour, and it comes with no money-back guarantee. If cost is your only consideration, a basic powder ticks that box. For most households — where the smell, the convenience, and having recourse if it doesn't work all matter — Septifix is the more complete answer, and it's the one we'd put in our own tank.",
